Let's cover some UMG fundamentals first and how to set up your interface in the scene

2
00:00:07.540 --> 00:00:08.780
that we'll be looking at today.

3
00:00:08.780 --> 00:00:15.080
So to get started, we can open a blank template and we can create an empty level to begin

4
00:00:15.080 --> 00:00:16.080
a project.

5
00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:21.600
And then what we can actually do is add a feature or content pack into the existing

6
00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:27.600
blank project so that we can just include some specific content for what we need today.

7
00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:33.160
So we're going to include the vehicle template asset and we'll just click add to project

8
00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:37.480
and this will give us access to this car model that you can see in the scene there.

9
00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:38.960
So it's a nice clean way to work.

10
00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:44.400
You don't have to come with all the bulk of other information from other content packs.

11
00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:49.080
